quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,133,"<span class=""h"">And<sup foot_note=""79800"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">hasten</span>towards forgiveness from your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord and a Garden as wide as the heavens and the earth, prepared for the mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>:"
  3,134,"those who spend in prosperity and adversity, and those who restrain<i class=""s"">(their) </i>rage, and those who forgive mankind—for Allah loves those who excel in doing good,"
  3,135,"and those who, when they commit an indecency or wrong themselves, remember Allah then ask forgiveness for their misdeeds—for who forgives misdeeds except Allah? And they do not persist in their wrongdoing while they know."
  3,136,"Those—their repayment is forgiveness from their Lord and Gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein, and how excellent is the reward of the workers!"
  3,137,"Many rules<i class=""s"">(God set) </i>for those before you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>have passed away, so journey through the earth and look what the outcome was for the disbelievers."
  3,138,"This is a proclamation to mankind, and guidance and an admonition for people who are mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>."
  3,139,"And do not waver nor grieve, for you are the highest as long as you are believers."
  3,140,"If a blow touches you, a similar blow has surely touched the<i class=""s"">(other) </i>people. For such days We alternate between mankind, and so that Allah{1}may know those who have attained faith and take witnesses{2}from among you. For Allah does not love the unjust.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.|2:The Arabic word used is shuhada’, which literally means ‘witnesses’ and is usually used to describe martyrs.
